[normal]Dr Fox[bold]: I think we have concerns about the amended ones. I am sure that comes up as one of the usual list of reforms. We would prefer the conditional approach, where you reject, subject to X, Y and Z being done, 
[normal]and then
[normal] you would be prepared to accept. I think there is an issue about doing amendables, and there are potential drafting consequences and difficulties that arise from that. Departments should have to do the heavy lifting; not 
[normal]Members
